User prompt basis:
PROMPT='%B[%n@%m:%~%b$(git_super_status)%B]%#%b '

Root prompt basis:
PROMPT='%B%m:%~%b$(git_super_status)%B%#%b '


PROMPT=$(henchman)

hm_prompt to build prompt, based upon hm_prompt (or hm_ps1?)

Use vcs_info to build individual parts in $vcs_info_msg_X_
use them later in $PROMPT

Items of interest:
* branch name (string)
* untracked files (flag)
* unstaged commits (count)
* staged commits (count)
* incoming commits (count/flag)
* outgoing commits (count/flag)
* smart mark (sigil)

Flags:
* #T tag
* #t time
* #b battery
* #p battery percentage
* #l load
* #S scree/tmux sessions
* #z sleeping jobs
* #& background jobs
* #[ screen/tmux enabled open [ flag
* #] screen/tmux enables close ] flag
* #@ X11 @
* #h (ssh/telnet) host
* #: read/write $PWD
* #~ $path (shortened)
* #P http proxy flag
* #v vcs status
* #? status
* #% prompt / smartmark
* ## #


Order:
1. Session tag (HM_TAG)
1. Time (HM_TIME)
1. Battery (charge/discharge)
1. Battery Charge %
1. System Load
1. Number of detached (tmux|screen) sessions
1. Number of sleeping jobs
1. Number of background jobs
1. Colored [] for inside (tmux|screen) session
    + How to deal with root theme?
1. Colored @ for lack-of-X11
1. Colored host if remote (ssh/telnet)
1. Colored : if $PWD is read-only
1. (Shortened) path
1. HTTP proxy symbol
1. VCS status
1. Colored $? if non-zero
1. Prompt (%/#/HG/git/whatever)

Root order:

1. Session tag
1. Time
1. Battery (charge/discharge)
1. Battery Charge %
1. System Load
1. Number of detached (tmux|screen) sessions
1. Number of sleeping jobs
1. Number of background jobs
1. tmux? x11
1. Colored host if remote (ssh/telnet)
1. Colored : if $PWD is read-only
1. (Shortened) path
1. HTTP proxy symbol
1. VCS status
1. Colored $? if non-zero
1. Prompt (%/#/HG/git/whatever)

Use "henchman" user context in vcs_info zstyles.

